    "pages.authorityGuidePages.clinicalApplicationPracticeAbgInterpretation": "Clinique Application: Pratique ABG Interpretation",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.clinicalAssessmentQuestionsCompriseApproximate": "Clinique évaluation questions comprise approximately 15-25% of infirmier licensing examens (NCLEX and REx-PN). These questions tester your ability to gather and interpret patient données, recognize anormal findings, and prioritize infirmier actions based activé évaluation résultats. The NCSBN Jugement clinique Measurement Modèle begins with \"Recognize Cues\" — which is fundamentally évaluation.",
