    "pages.authorityGuidePages.copdLowflowO12Lmin": "COPD: faible-flow O₂ (1-2 L/min, cible SpO₂ 88-92%). Do NOT give élevé-flow O₂ — removes hypoxic respiratoire drive",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.copdMostCommonObesityHypoventilation": "COPD (most courant), obesity hypoventilation syndrome, kyphoscoliosis, chronique neuromuscular troubles",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.copdPatientsAreChronicCo": "COPD patients are chronique CO₂ retainers. Their respiratoire drive depends activé hypoxia, not CO₂ niveaux. Giving élevé-flow O₂ eliminates the hypoxic drive and can cause respiratoire arrest. Always use faible-flow O₂ targeting SpO₂ 88-92%.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.correctSlowlyNoMoreThan": "Correct slowly: no plus than 8-12 mEq/L per 24 heures to prevent osmotic demyelination syndrome (ODS)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.cracklesFluidatelectasisWheezesBronchospas": "Crackles (fluid/atelectasis), wheezes (bronchospasm), stridor (upper voies aériennes), pleural friction rub",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.cranialNerves": "Cranial nerves:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.cushingSyndromeCorticosteroidExcess": "Cushing syndrome / corticosteroid excess",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.cushingsTriad": "Cushing's triad",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.d5wIsIsotonicInThe": "D5W is isotonic in the bag but becomes hypotonic once infused (the dextrose is rapidly metabolized, leaving gratuit water). Therefore, D5W should NOT be used for patients with increased ICP or those at risque for cerebral œdème. This distinction is commonly tested.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.dailyWeightSameTimeSame": "Daily poids (same temps, same scale, same clothing), I&O, poumon sounds (crackles), JVD, pedal œdème, activité tolerance",
