    "pages.authorityGuidePages.headacheConfusionDrowsinessProgressingTo": "Headache, confusion, drowsiness progressing to coma, warm flushed skin (CO₂ vasodilation), tachycardia, dysrhythmias. In chronique COPD: elevated HCO₃⁻ indicates rénal compensation.",
