    "pages.authorityGuidePages.hypoparathyroidismChronicKidneyDiseasePancre": "Hypoparathyroidism, chronique kidney maladie, pancreatitis, inadequate vitamin D, hypomagnesemia, massive blood transfusions (citrate binds calcium), thyroidectomy",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.hypotensionBradycardiaDiffersFromOther": "Hypotension + Bradycardia (differs from autre choc types which afficher tachycardia)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.hypotensionTachycardiaTachypneaAlteredMe": "Hypotension + Tachycardia + Tachypnea + Altered mental statut → immediate intervention",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.hypotonicFluidsMonitorNeuroStatus": "Hypotonic liquides + moniteur neuro statut",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.hypoxemiaPePneumoniaAltitudeCompensatory": "Hypoxemia (PE, pneumonia, altitude) — compensatory hyperventilation",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.iabeticKetoacidosisDkaMostCommonly": "iabetic ketoacidosis (DKA) — most commonly tested",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ifHypoxiadrivenTreatTheHypoxemia": "If hypoxia-driven: treat the hypoxemia (oxygène thérapie, PE gestion)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ifTheActualCompensationIs": "If the actual compensation is plus or less than expected, a mixed trouble is present. For exemple, a patient with DKA (metabolic acidosis) and pneumonia (respiratoire acidosis) would have les deux faible HCO₃⁻ AND élevé CO₂ — the pH would be very faible because les deux systèmes are contributing to acidosis.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.improveVentilationPositionUprightHigh": "Améliorer ventilation: position upright (élevé Fowler's), incentive spirometry, assist with breathing exercices",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.inClinicalPracticeAndOn": "In Pratique clinique and activé avancé examen questions, patients may have two or plus acid-base troubles simultaneously. Recognizing mixed troubles requires understanding expected compensation ranges.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.inFullyCompensatedAbgsThe": "In fully compensated ABGs, the pH is normal but les deux CO₂ and HCO₃⁻ are anormal. To determine the primaire trouble, look at which side of 7.40 the pH falls. If pH is 7.35-7.39, the primaire trouble is acidosis. If pH is 7.41-7.45, the primaire trouble is alkalosis.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.includeRelevantNegativesNoJvd": "Inclure relevant negatives. \"No JVD, no peripheral edema\" is clinically important information",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.increasedIcp": "Increased ICP:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.increasedIcpHypertensionWideningPulse": "(increased ICP): Hypertension (widening pouls pressure) + Bradycardia + Irregular respirations → neurosurgical Urgence",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.increasedIntracranialPressureWorsensCerebral": "Increased intracranial pressure (worsens cerebral œdème), burns (third-spacing), hypovolemia",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.inspectAuscultatePercussPalpateAuscultate": "Inspect, Auscultate, Percuss, Palpate (auscultate BEFORE palpation to avoid stimulating bowel sounds)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.inspection": "Inspection:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.integumentaryAssessment": "Tégumentaire Évaluation",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.intenseThirstDryMucousMembranes": "Intense thirst, dry mucous membranes, flushed skin, faible-note fièvre, restlessness, irritability, muscle twitching, seizures (severe)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.isTheOtherValueAlso": "Is the autre valeur also anormal? If yes, the corps is compensating. If the autre valeur is normal, the trouble is uncompensated.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.isotonicInTheBagBecomes": "— isotonic in the bag, becomes hypotonic once dextrose is metabolized. Used for médicament dilution and maintenance hydration.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.isotonicSolutionsSameOsmolalityAs": "Isotonic Solutions (Same osmolality as blood: ~275-295 mOsm/L)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivCalciumGluconateAirwayEquipment": "IV calcium gluconate + voies aériennes equipment at bedside",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivFluidResuscitationIsotonicCrystalloid": "IV liquide resuscitation (isotonic crystalloid for DKA and septicémie)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivMagnesiumSulfateForSevere": "IV magnesium sulfate for severe depletion — administrer slowly, moniteur DTRs, respiratoire évaluer, and urine sortie",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivNormalSalineForChlorideresponsive": "IV normal saline for chloride-responsive alkalosis (restores volume and chloride)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivNormalSalineHydrationAggressive": "IV normal saline hydration (aggressive) — dilutes calcium and promotes rénal excretion",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivPotassiumAlwaysDilutedAlways": "IV potassium: always diluted, always via pump, never by push",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivPotassiumNeverGiveBy": "IV potassium: NEVER give by IV push — maximum évaluer 10-20 mEq/hour via perfusion pump with cardiaque surveillance",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivPotassiumPushCausesFatal": "IV potassium push causes fatal cardiaque arrest. This is one of the most commonly tested sécurité questions activé the NCLEX. Always administrer IV potassium diluted and infused slowly with cardiaque surveillance. Never ajouter KCl to a hanging IV bag — always use premixed solutions or perfusion pump.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ivSodiumOrPotassiumPhosphate": "IV sodium or potassium phosphate for severe deficiency — infuse slowly",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.jvd": "JVD:",
