    "pages.authorityGuidePages.lightheadednessDizzinessTinglingnumbnessCir": "Lightheadedness, dizziness, tingling/numbness (circumoral and extremities), muscle cramps, tetany (alkalosis decreases ionized calcium), palpitations, syncope.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.loopAndThiazideDiureticsMost": "Loop and thiazide diuretics (most courant), vomiting, NG suction, diarrhea, alkalosis, insuline administration, excessive laxative use",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.loopDiureticsFurosemideAfterAdequate": "Loop diuretics (furosemide) after adequate hydration — promotes calciuresis",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.lowphosphorusDietLimitDairyCola": "Faible-phosphorus diet: limit dairy, cola, processed meats, nuts",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.lungsRespiratory": "Poumons (respiratoire):",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.magnesiumIsCriticalForNeuromuscular": "Magnesium is critique for neuromuscular fonction and is closely linked to potassium and calcium balance. Hypomagnesemia must be corrected before hypokalemia will respond to traitement — this is a élevé-yield examen concept.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.magnesiumMgNormalRange1525": "Magnesium (Mg²⁺) — Plage normale: 1.5-2.5 mEq/L",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.maslowsHierarchyOfNeeds": "Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.measureBpAndHrSupine": "Mesurer BP and HR supine, then standing (or sitting if Impossible de stand). Positif orthostatic hypotension: SBP drop ≥ 20 mmHg OR DBP drop ≥ 10 mmHg OR HR increase ≥ 20 bpm within 3 minutes. Indicates volume depletion or autonomic dysfunction. Infirmier action: ensure sécurité (fall precautions), rapport to fournisseur, hold antihypertensives as appropriate.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.mechanicalVentilationRateOrTidal": "Mechanical ventilation (évaluer or tidal volume définir too élevé)",
