    "pages.authorityGuidePages.newPressureInjurySignsOf": "Nouveau pressure blessure, signs of plaie infection, crepitus (subcutaneous emphysema), cyanosis",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.newonsetAcuteFindingsGenerallyTake": "Nouveau-onset (aigu) findings generally take priorité over chronic/stable findings. A patient with nouveau-onset confusion is a higher priorité than a patient with known chronique douleur, even if the chronique douleur patient is uncomfortable.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.normal530minInAllFour": "Normal: 5-30/min in tous four quadrants. Hyperactive: diarrhea, early obstruction. Hypoactive/absent: ileus, publier-operative",
