    "pages.authorityGuidePages.postthyroidectomyAssessForChvosteksAnd": "Publier-thyroidectomy: assess for Chvostek's and Trousseau's signs every 4 heures for 48 heures",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.potassiumIsTheMostAbundant": "Potassium is the most abundant intracellular cation and is critique for cardiaque conduction, neuromuscular fonction, and acid-base balance. Les deux hypokalemia and hyperkalemia can cause life-threatening cardiaque dysrhythmias, making potassium the most frequently tested Électrolyte activé infirmier examens. ECG changes are a priorité évaluation finding.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.practiceWithExamstyleQuestionsAnd": "Pratique with examen-style questions and détaillé clinique rationales.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.preferredForSurgicalPatientsAnd": "— preferred for chirurgical patients and burns (Parkland formule). Contains Électrolytes (Na, K, Ca, lactate). Contraindicated in foie échec (cannot metabolize lactate) and hyperkalemia.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.pregnancyProgesteroneStimulatesRespiration": "Pregnancy (progesterone stimulates respiration)",
