    "pages.authorityGuidePages.refeedingSyndromeIsALifethreatening": "Refeeding syndrome is a life-threatening complication of rapidly restarting nutrition in malnourished patients. As cells take up glucose, phosphorus, potassium, and magnesium shift intracellularly causing dangerous drops. This is heavily tested in contexte of eating trouble patients and prolonged NPO statut.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.refeedingSyndromeMostCommonlyTested": "Refeeding syndrome (most commonly tested), chronique alcoholism, diabetic ketoacidosis récupération (insuline drives PO₄ into cells), phosphate-binding antacids, respiratoire alkalosis",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.refeedingSyndromePreventionAdvanceNutrition": "Refeeding syndrome prévention: advance nutrition gradually in malnourished patients",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.regularInsulinD50IvDrives": "Regular insuline + D50 IV — drives K⁺ into cells (temporary, moniteur glucose closely)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.regulateCoLevelsWithinMinutes": "Regulate CO₂ niveaux within minutes. Hyperventilation blows désactivé CO₂ (raises pH). Hypoventilation retains CO₂ (lowers pH). CO₂ is an acid when dissolved in blood (forms carbonic acid, H₂CO₃).",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.regulateHcoBicarbonateLevelsOver": "Regulate HCO₃⁻ (bicarbonate) niveaux over heures to jours. The kidneys can either retain or excrete bicarbonate and hydrogen ions. This is a slower but plus sustained compensatory mécanisme.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.reinforceKeyConceptsWithSpacedrepetition": "Reinforce Concepts clés with spaced-repetition cartes mémoire.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.relatedResources": "Ressources connexes",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.rememberStonesBonesGroansMoans": "Remember \"stones, bones, groans, moans\" — kidney stones, bone douleur, abdominal pain/constipation, confusion/lethargy. Shortened QT, cardiaque arrest at severe niveaux.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.remiaRenalFailureCannotExcrete": "remia (rénal échec — cannot excrete acids)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.renalFailureCannotExcreteExcessive": "Rénal échec (cannot excrete), excessive magnesium-containing antacids/laxatives, preeclampsia traitement (magnesium sulfate toxicité)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.renalFailureCannotExcreteExcessive2": "Rénal échec (cannot excrete), excessive phosphorus intake, hypoparathyroidism, tumeur lysis syndrome, rhabdomyolysis",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.renalFailureMostCommonPotassiumsparing": "Rénal échec (most courant), potassium-sparing diuretics, ACE inhibitors, tissu trauma/burns, acidosis, hemolyzed blood échantillon (false elevation)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.renalTubularAcidosis": "Rénal tubular acidosis",
