    "pages.authorityGuidePages.sodiumBicarbonateIvShiftsK": "Sodium bicarbonate IV — shifts K⁺ intracellularly in metabolic acidosis",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.sodiumIsTheMostAbundant": "Sodium is the most abundant extracellular cation and the primaire determinant of serum osmolality. Sodium imbalances are fundamentally water balance troubles — hyponatremia usually reflects water excess, while hypernatremia reflects water deficit.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.softNontenderNondistendedReboundTendernes": "Soft, non-tender, non-distended. Rebound tenderness = peritoneal irritation (Urgence)",
