    "pages.authorityGuidePages.tetanyTrousseausChvosteksThinkCalcium": "(tetany, Trousseau's, Chvostek's) → think calcium or magnesium deficit",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.theMostFundamentalPrioritizationFramework": "The most fondamental prioritization framework. Always adresse voies aériennes problèmes premier, then breathing, then circulation. Activé the NCLEX, if one patient has an voies aériennes problème and another has a circulation problème, the voies aériennes patient is always the priorité.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.theNclexLovesPatientSafety": "The NCLEX loves Sécurité du patient questions involving Électrolytes:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.theRomeMethodIsThe": "The ROME méthode is the most reliable systematic approach to ABG interpretation activé infirmier examens. It eliminates guesswork and works for every ABG scénario.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.theStudyGuideYouAre": "The Guide d'étude you are looking for does not exist.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.theTwoRegulators": "The Two Regulators",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.thyleneGlycolPoisoning": "thylene glycol poisoning",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.thyroidStorm": "Thyroid storm:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.timely": "Timely:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.toSucceedWithElectrolyteQuestions": "To succeed with Électrolyte questions, you need to understand three things for each Électrolyte: (1) the Plage normale and what drives it up or down, (2) the clinique signs and symptômes of les deux excess and deficit, and (3) the priorité infirmier interventions including surveillance, médicament administration, and Sécurité du patient measures.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.treatTheUnderlyingCauseAntiemetics": "Treat the underlying cause: antiemetics for vomiting, remplacer NG losses with appropriate liquides",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.treatTheUnderlyingCauseInsulin": "Treat the underlying cause (insuline for DKA, antibiotiques for septicémie, dialysis for rénal échec)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.treatUnderlyingCauseAnalgesicsFor": "Treat underlying cause: analgesics for douleur, antipyretics for fièvre, anxiolytics for anxiety",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.trousseausSignCarpalSpasmWith": "Trousseau's signer (carpal spasm with BP cuff inflation), Chvostek's signer (facial twitching activé tapping facial nerve), tetany, laryngospasm, seizures, prolonged QT interval",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.uncompensated": "Uncompensated:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.understandingIvFluidTonicityIs": "Understanding IV liquide tonicity is essentiel for managing Électrolyte imbalances safely. Selecting the wrong IV liquide can worsen the imbalance and cause harm — this is why IV liquide questions are courant activé infirmier examens.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.unexpectedFindingsRequireActionExpected": "Unexpected findings exiger action; expected findings exiger surveillance. If a publier-chirurgical patient rapports mild incisional douleur (expected), that is lower priorité than a patient reporting sudden chest tightness (unexpected). Know Qu'est-ce que expected for each condition so you can recognize the unexpected.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.unstablePatientsAlwaysTakePriority": "Unstable patients always take priorité. Stable patients can attendre, can often be delegated, and are appropriate for infirmier assistants to moniteur. Unstable patients exiger RN évaluation and intervention.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.ureterosigmoidostomy": "Ureterosigmoidostomy",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.urineCharacteristics": "Urine characteristics:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.urineOutput": "Urine sortie:",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.useApprovedAbbreviationsOnlyIf": "Use approuvé abbreviations only. If you make an erreur, draw a single line through it, écrire \"erreur,\" initial, and date — never use white-out or scribble over",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.useMeasurableTermsWound3": "Use measurable conditions. \"Plaie 3 cm x 2 cm with serous drainage\" is better than \"plaie looks good\"",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.usedForHypernatremiaCellularDehydration": "— used for hypernatremia, cellular déshydratation. Liquide shifts FROM vasculaire space INTO cells.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.usedForHypoglycemiaTreatment": "— used for hypoglycemia traitement",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.usedForSevereSymptomaticHyponatremia": "— used for severe symptomatic hyponatremia with seizures. Liquide shifts FROM cells INTO vasculaire space.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.viaInfusionPumpOnlyCentral": "Via perfusion pump only, central line preferred, frequent sodium surveillance (every 2-4 heures)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.vitalSignPatternsToRecognize": "Vital Signer Modèles to Recognize",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.vitalSignsAreTheMost": "Signes vitaux are the most basique and most critique évaluation données. Knowing normal ranges, understanding what deviations mean, and recognizing life-threatening vital signer modèles is essentiel for les deux examen succès and Pratique clinique.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.vomitingngSuctioningLossOfHcl": "Vomiting/NG suctioning (loss of HCl from stomach — most commonly tested)",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.whenAnExamQuestionPresents": "When an examen question presents multiple patients with anormal Signes vitaux, use the ABCs (Voies aériennes, Breathing, Circulation) to prioritize. A patient with respiratoire distress (SpO₂ 82%, RR 32) takes priorité over a patient with fièvre (38.8°C) or mild tachycardia (HR 105).",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.whichAssessmentFindingIndicatesOr": "— \"Which évaluation finding indicates...\" or \"The infirmier(ère) should assess for which complication?\"",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.whichAssessmentFindingRequiresImmediate": "— \"Which évaluation finding requires immediate intervention?\" or \"Which patient should the infirmier(ère) see premier?\"",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.whichValueCoOrHco": "Which valeur (CO₂ or HCO₃⁻) explains the pH direction? That is the primaire trouble.",
    "pages.authorityGuidePages.wounds": "Wounds:",
